paid executive f ross johnson us as part of a golden handshake clause the largest such deal in history at the time as severance compensation for his acceptance of the kkr takeover he used the money to open his own investment firm rjm group inc in  rjr nabisco spun off rj reynolds tobacco which began trading on june  as rj reynolds tobacco holdings inc and a year later announced it would buy nabisco group holdings inc the company that had been rjr nabisco this followed the sale of nabisco holdings group to philip morris recent historyedit reynolds american inc building in downtown winstonsalem nc in  then ceo james johnston testified under oath before congress saying that he didnt believe that nicotine is addictive in  the company was part of the tobacco master settlement agreement with  us states agreeing to pay smokingrelated health care costs and restrict advertising in return for protection against private lawsuits in  rj reynolds was spun out of rjr nabisco the same year the company sold all its nonus operations to japan tobacco which made those operations into its international arm jt international consequently any camels winstons or salems sold outside the us are now actually japanese cigarettes in  the company was fined m for handing out free cigarettes at events attended by children and was fined m for breaking the  master agreement which restricted targeting youth in its tobacco advertisements in  the european union was involved in three civil suits against rj reynolds in the united states district court for the eastern district of new york accusing the company of selling black market cigarettes to drug traffickers and mobsters from italy russia colombia and the balkans the suits were unsuccessful on july   rj reynolds merged with the us operations of british american tobacco operating under the name of brown  williamson a new parent holding company reynolds american inc was established as part of the transaction in may  former rj reynolds vicepresident of sales stan smith pleaded guilty to charges of defrauding the canadian government of  cdn through a cigarette smuggling operation smith confessed to overseeing the s operation while employed by rjr canadianbrand cigarettes were smuggled out of and back into canada or smuggled from puerto rico and sold on the black market to avoid taxes the judge referred to it as biggest fraud case in canadian history since  rj reynolds has been the subject of a farm labor organizing committee floc campaign to reduce the exploitative nature of its tobacco procurement system flocs goal is to meet with reynolds executives growers and workers in collective bargaining to improve farmworkers pay and living conditions although there are many layers of subcontractors within the procurement system that seemingly absolve reynolds of responsibility floc asserts that its executives have the ability to make changes within the system due to their wealth and enormous power despite repeated refusals to meet from ceo susan ivey floc continues the campaign against rj reynolds tobacco company in  reynolds american announced that the company would close its manufacturing plants in winstonsalem nc and puerto rico production from these plants will be moved to the tobaccoville nc plant on july   reynolds american agreed to buy lorillard tobacco company for  billion the deal also included the sale of the kool winston salem and blu brands to imperial tobacco for  billion in january  reynolds american agreed to a  billion deal to be taken over by british american tobacco marketing sponsorships and criticismsedit from  rj reynolds was a title sponsor of the nhra winston drag racing series the nascar winston cup series and until  the imsa camel gt for sportscars the nhra sponsorship lasted up to  before a new governing rule stated the master settlement agreement restricting rj reynolds to one sponsorship of a sporting event as a result they chose nascar which lasted up to  the lotus formula one team was sponsored by camel from  until  rjr brand winston was a sponsor of the  fifa world cup whilst fellow brand camel was a sponsor of the  fifa world cup joe cameledit in  rjr resurrected the mascot for their camel brand of cigarette joe camel joe camel an anthropomorphic cartoon camel wearing sunglasses was claimed to be a ploy to entice and interest the underaged in smoking rj reynolds maintained that joes smooth character was meant only to appeal to adult smokers this criticism was reinforced by a  study published in the journal of the american medical association  showing that more children  and  years old could recognize joe camel than could recognize mickey mouse or fred flintstone coincidentally fred flintstone was also once used to sell rj reynolds winston cigarettes and alleged that the joe camel advertisement campaign was targeting children despite rj reynolds contention that the campaign had been researched only among adults and was directed only at the smokers of other brands in response to this criticism rjr instituted lets clear the air on smoking a campaign of fullpage advertisements consisting entirely of large type text which denied the charges and declared that smoking is an adult custom in late  rj reynolds opened the marshall mcgearty lounge in the wicker park neighborhood of chicago as part of a marketing strategy to promote a brand of superpremium cigarettes and counteract local smoking bans in restaurants and cafes that took effect in  the lounge which offers thirteen varieties of exclusive handcrafted cigarette along with alcohol and light food has been well received in the neighborhood and by the targeted upscale market according to company officials the lounge has since been closed due to chicago indoor smoking restrictions the company planned to open a second location in winstonsalem in the summer of  but scrapped those plans within weeks of opening citing the increasing number of smoking restrictions in public places by state and local governments lawsuitsedit in may  a miamidade circuit jury awarded julie reese an yearold cape coral smoker represented by the ferraro law firm a total verdict of  million from rj reynolds tobacco after she developed laryngeal cancer and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease the jury found reynolds to be negligent guilty of fraud by concealment and fraud conspiracy and guilty of placing a defective product on the market brandsedit rj reynolds brands include newport camel doral eclipse kent and pall mall brands still manufactured but no longer receiving significant marketing support include barclay belair capri carlton gpc lucky strike misty monarch more now tareyton vantage and viceroy the company also manufactures certain privatelabel brands five of the companys brands are among the top ten best selling cigarette brands in the united states and it is estimated that one in three cigarettes sold in the country were manufactured by rj reynolds tobacco company in  rj reynolds acquired the rights to the smokeless tobacco products kodiak and grizzly dip uptownedit in  rj reynolds planned to launch a new cigarette brand called uptown aimed primarily at africanamericans to appeal to blacks seeking a less pronounced menthol taste similar to lorillards newport which was gaining share reynolds decided against using green on the packaging and instead used black and gold the colors of luxury european cigarettes narrowing the marketing further uptown cigarettes were to be packed with filters facing down the reverse of the usual arrangement  market research indicated that many blacks open packs from the bottom possibly to avoid crushing the filters it was later discovered that cigarette packs were opened from the bottom for a different reason this phenomenon traces back at least to world war ii when cigarettes were a valued commodity among soldiers often a soldier temporarily without cigarettes and without funds would bum a smoke from a fellow soldier it was impolite to refuse such a request however there were two occasions when a refusal was not considered impolite if there was only one cigarette left in the pack and if the pack was not yet opened a pack opened from the bottom and resting as it normally did in a shirt pocket would appear unopened therefore the soldier in possession of cigarettes would be able to avoid having to give too many away the promotional blitz was scheduled to begin on feb  and philadelphia was selected as the test market because of its large black population before it began the campaign came under fire from religious health and blackinterest groups who expressed concerns about promoting cigarette smoking to blacks on january   reynolds abruptly decided to cancel the cigarette saying that the test marketing would no longer be reliable because of what it called the unfair and biased attention that brand has received facilitiesedit reynolds building entrance in winstonsalem nc the companys headquarters were located in the reynolds building in winstonsalem for more than fifty years built in  the story building was designed by the same architects shreve  lamb who later designed the empire state building in new york city built in  at a cost of  million  million in  dollars the whitaker park plant had  square feet of manufacturing space and was considered the worlds largest and most modern cigarettemanufacturing plant it was announced in may  that cigarette manufacturing would cease at whitaker park by mid this had been done manufacturing formerly performed at the whitaker park plant was consolidated in the moremodern tobaccoville plant on january   reynolds announced that whitaker park was being donated to whitaker park development authority inc started in april  by winstonsalem business inc the winstonsalem alliance and wake forest university in september  rj reynolds industries moved the first of  headquarters employees into the notyetcompleted  million squarefoot glass and steel world headquarters building being built across reynolds boulevard from the whitaker park plant at the same time the company had plans for a new skyscraper downtown the current headquarters the rjr plaza building is  stories tall and was completed in  adjacent to the original  reynolds building the tobacco company moved its headquarters to rjr plaza in  and the  building continued to be used for some company offices until  the older building stood vacant until new owners in  began the process to convert it to a hotel with the parent company renamed rjr nabisco in  after merging with nabisco planning to move its headquarters to atlanta in september  the company donated the world headquarters building to wake forest university in january  and in july of that year the company voted to move its planterslife savers division to onethird of that building in  the buildings tenants were aon corporation bbt and pepsico on november  of that year pepsi announced  new jobs and a  million expansion of university corporate center with bbt moving two of its operations to reynolda business center aon and pepsi remained the primary occupants in  reynolds building in downtown winstonsalem nc rj reynolds largest plant tobaccoville a  million square foot  m² facility constructed in  is located in the town of tobaccoville north carolina near winstonsalem macon manufacturing located in macon ga resides in a  million square foot  m² facility built in  this manufacturing plant was formerly known as brown  williamson which was purchased by reynolds and eventually closed in  rj reynolds has a tobaccosheet manufacturing operation in winstonsalem the sheet manufacturing operation in chester va was closed in  also there are leaf operations in wilson nc tobaccostorage facilities in blacksburg sc and richmond va and a significant researchanddevelopment facility in winstonsalem a manufacturing plant in puerto rico was closed in  among these facilities rj reynolds employs approximately  people rj reynolds subsidiary rj reynolds tobacco foreign sales corporation is established in the british virgin islands to minimize its tax liability see alsoedit project scum notesedit  a b frank tursi susan e white and steve mcquilkin  in the belly of the beast winstonsalem journal   who we are rjrtcom reynolds american  retrieved  may    a b c d e f g h i j k l m n tursi frank  winstonsalem a history john f blair publisher pp –  –   burrough bryan  barbarians at the gate harpercollins p    debbie norton february   reynolds to spin off sealand starnews   a b c a stock history – sequence of events pdf retrieved    burrough bryan john helyar  barbarians at the gate the fall of rjr nabisco new york harpercollins p  isbn  retrieved  june    the high cost of parting ways with ceos cbc news  june  archived from the original on november   retrieved  june    mike billips  july  sons mind moguls money atlanta business chronicle retrieved  june    hilts philip j april   tobacco chiefs say cigarettes arent addictive the new york times   bbc tobacco companies tell kids dont smoke retrieved    helena keers rj reynolds faces third eu suit november   telegraph  rj reynolds wins dismissal of european communitys rico claims march  jones day  henry weinstein and myron levin rj reynolds accused of black market deals october   los angeles times  tracey a basler cigarettes smuggling and terror the european community v rj reynolds   jicl   senior exec wont go to jail in massive fraud case cbc news may    collins kristin farm union targets rjr news  observer october     rj reynolds closing plant  bray michael j de la merced and chad to compete with altria reynolds american is buying lorillard retrieved  october    mangan dan july   feeling blu ecig company spun off in major tobacco deal cnbc   british american tobacco agrees to pay  billion to take full control of reynolds american the wall street journal january   retrieved january     httpwwwfifacommmdocumentfifafactsmiscfwcpartnfsfwcpartnerspdf  fischer pm schwartz mp richards jw jr goldstein ao