he summer of  but scrapped those plans within weeks of opening citing the increasing number of smoking restrictions in public places by state and local governments lawsuitsedit in may  a miamidade circuit jury awarded julie reese an yearold cape coral smoker represented by the ferraro law firm a total verdict of  million from rj reynolds tobacco after she developed laryngeal cancer and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease the jury found reynolds to be negligent guilty of fraud by concealment and fraud conspiracy and guilty of placing a defective product on the market brandsedit rj reynolds brands include newport camel doral eclipse kent and pall mall brands still manufactured but no longer receiving significant marketing support include barclay belair capri carlton gpc lucky strike misty monarch more now tareyton vantage and viceroy the company also manufactures certain privatelabel brands five of the companys brands are among the top ten best selling cigarette brands in the united states and it is estimated that one in three cigarettes sold in the country were manufactured by rj reynolds tobacco company in  rj reynolds acquired the rights to the smokeless tobacco products kodiak and grizzly dip uptownedit in  rj reynolds planned to launch a new cigarette brand called uptown aimed primarily at africanamericans to appeal to blacks seeking a less pronounced menthol taste similar to lorillards newport which was gaining share reynolds decided against using green on the packaging and instead used black and gold the colors of luxury european cigarettes narrowing the marketing further uptown cigarettes were to be packed with filters facing down the reverse of the usual arrangement  market research indicated that many blacks open packs from the bottom possibly to avoid crushing the filters it was later discovered that cigarette packs were opened from the bottom for a different reason this phenomenon traces back at least to world war ii when cigarettes were a valued commodity among soldiers often a soldier temporarily without cigarettes and without funds would bum a smoke from a fellow soldier it was impolite to refuse such a request however there were two occasions when a refusal was not considered impolite if there was only one cigarette left in the pack and if the pack was not yet opened a pack opened from the bottom and resting as it normally did in a shirt pocket would appear unopened therefore the soldier in possession of cigarettes would be able to avoid having to give too many away the promotional blitz was scheduled to begin on feb  and philadelphia was selected as the test market because of its large black population before it began the campaign came under fire from religious health and blackinterest groups who expressed concerns about promoting cigarette smoking to blacks on january   reynolds abruptly decided to cancel the cigarette saying that the test marketing would no longer be reliable because of what it called the unfair and biased attention that brand has received facilitiesedit reynolds building entrance in winstonsalem nc the companys headquarters were located in the reynolds building in winstonsalem for more than fifty years built in  the story building was designed by the same architects shreve  lamb who later designed the empire state building in new york city built in  at a cost of  million  million in  dollars the whitaker park plant had  square feet of manufacturing space and was considered the worlds largest and most modern cigarettemanufacturing plant it was announced in may  that cigarette manufacturing would cease at whitaker park by mid this had been done manufacturing formerly performed at the whitaker park plant was consolidated in the moremodern tobaccoville plant on january   reynolds announced that whitaker park was being donated to whitaker park development authority inc started in april  by winstonsalem business inc the winstonsalem alliance and wake forest university in september  rj reynolds industries moved the first of  headquarters employees into the notyetcompleted  million squarefoot glass and steel world headquarters building being built across reynolds boulevard from the whitaker park plant at the same time the company had plans for a new skyscraper downtown the current headquarters the rjr plaza building is  stories tall and was completed in  adjacent to the original  reynolds building the tobacco company moved its headquarters to rjr plaza in  and the  building continued to be used for some company offices until  the older building stood vacant until new owners in  began the process to convert it to a hotel with the parent company renamed rjr nabisco in  after merging with nabisco planning to move its headquarters to atlanta in september  the company donated the world headquarters building to wake forest university in january  and in july of that year the company voted to move its planterslife savers division to onethird of that building in  the buildings tenants were aon corporation bbt and pepsico on november  of that year pepsi announced  new jobs and a  million expansion of university corporate center with bbt moving two of its operations to reynolda business center aon and pepsi remained the primary occupants in  reynolds building in downtown winstonsalem nc rj reynolds largest plant tobaccoville a  million square foot  m² facility constructed in  is located in the town of tobaccoville north carolina near winstonsalem macon manufacturing located in macon ga resides in a  million square foot  m² facility built in  this manufacturing plant was formerly known as brown  williamson which was purchased by reynolds and eventually closed in  rj reynolds has a tobaccosheet manufacturing operation in winstonsalem the sheet manufacturing operation in chester va was closed in  also there are leaf operations in wilson nc tobaccostorage facilities in blacksburg sc and richmond va and a significant researchanddevelopment facility in winstonsalem a manufacturing plant in puerto rico was closed in  among these facilities rj reynolds employs approximately  people rj reynolds subsidiary rj reynolds tobacco foreign sales corporation is established in the british virgin islands to minimize its tax liability see alsoedit project scum notesedit  a b frank tursi susan e white and steve mcquilkin  in the belly of the beast winstonsalem journal   who we are rjrtcom reynolds american  retrieved  may    a b c d e f g h i j k l m n tursi frank  winstonsalem a history john f blair publisher pp –  –   burrough bryan  barbarians at the gate harpercollins p    debbie norton february   reynolds to spin off sealand starnews   a b c a stock history – sequence of events pdf retrieved    burrough bryan john helyar  barbarians at the gate the fall of rjr nabisco new york harpercollins p  isbn  retrieved  june    the high cost of parting ways with ceos cbc news  june  archived from the original on november   retrieved  june    mike billips  july  sons mind moguls money atlanta business chronicle retrieved  june    hilts philip j april   tobacco chiefs say cigarettes arent addictive the new york times   bbc tobacco companies tell kids dont smoke retrieved    helena keers rj reynolds faces third eu suit november   telegraph  rj reynolds wins dismissal of european communitys rico claims march  jones day  henry weinstein and myron levin rj reynolds accused of black market deals october   los angeles times  tracey a basler cigarettes smuggling and terror the european community v rj reynolds   jicl   senior exec wont go to jail in massive fraud case cbc news may    collins kristin farm union targets rjr news  observer october     rj reynolds closing plant  bray michael j de la merced and chad to compete with altria reynolds american is buying lorillard retrieved  october    mangan dan july   feeling blu ecig company spun off in major tobacco deal cnbc   british american tobacco agrees to pay  billion to take full control of reynolds american the w